White House Press Secretary Robert Gibbs briefed the media on May 29, 2009. He discussed the upcoming hurricane season and the steps people should take to be prepared. He also addressed concerns about the state of the economy and the restructuring of General Motors. Gibbs mentioned that the President would be traveling to Saudi Arabia, Egypt, Germany, and France in the coming week. He also talked about the importance of improving relations with the Muslim world and the need for healthcare reform. The briefing concluded with a discussion on the nomination of Sonia Sotomayor to the Supreme Court and the collection of stories to support healthcare reform.